{
  "stem": "13395.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 4.1,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You had 'Juden Verboten.' There were many places, many hotels, where my aunt used to spend their summer-- her summers in the mountains in the different [INAUDIBLE].",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "Some hotels would no longer accept her reservation.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And these are the stories I always heard being told.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "The schools, Jewish students, you were no longer allowed into a German university.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So slowly, the Jews were isolated from mainstream.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "As it-- as the years went on, Jews were no longer allowed to have their own businesses.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "Every Jewish business got a German manager, but the Jew was still responsible for the success of the business.",
      "word_count": 19
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 1,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 15,
      "text": "And if the business didn't do well, they were punished and fined for the losses that were incurred by the German manager.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "In our family, there was one intermarriage.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 2,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "My father's half brother.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "His name was Walter Kaufman, because he was-- my grandmother remarried, and the name was Kaufman.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "He married a non-Jewish woman.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "My mother never accepted intermarriage, and she would not have.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "But she-- it wasn't her son that married a non-Jewish woman.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "But there was intermarriage.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And they were very good marriages.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 3,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And many non-Jews-- non-Jewish people saved their spouses during the war in Germany.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, they weren't.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had Jewish-- they had non-Jewish friends.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "They had-- there were Jewish organizations that were connected to the synagogues.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "There were youth groups.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And Jews were organized through the synagogues, especially.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "Well, in big cities, the Jewish kids had the-- the opportunity to belong to a Jewish organization.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I was always envious of that.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But then they were forbidden.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 4,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "You-- during the Nazi time, you could no longer belong to a Jewish organization.",
      "word_count": 14
    }
  ],
